# Roo-Code Global Rules

## Code Quality
- Write clean, self-documenting code. Avoid redundant comments.
- Prefer small, focused functions over monolithic blocks.
- Handle errors explicitly — never swallow exceptions silently.

## Git Discipline
- Write meaningful commit messages in imperative mood (e.g., "Add user auth middleware").
- Keep commits atomic: one logical change per commit.

## Security
- Never hardcode secrets, API keys, or credentials.
- Validate and sanitize all external input.
- Use environment variables for configuration that varies by deployment.

## Documentation
- Every public function/method must have a clear docstring or JSDoc comment.
- Update the README when adding new features or changing setup steps.
